1
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:06,640
♪

2
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:07,641
Take this.

3
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:08,742
I want you to have it.

4
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:10,677
Huh?

5
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:13,280
♪

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:15,349
Listen up, you can do it.

7
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:16,817
Picture yourself
big and strong

8
00:00:16,817 --> 00:00:18,385
like the warrior
on that card.

9
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:20,020
Mm.

10
00:00:21,188 --> 00:00:22,656
You've got to
believe in yourself,

11
00:00:22,656 --> 00:00:24,858
that way nobody can ever
stop you from becoming

12
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:27,928
the stronger person
you want to be.

13
00:00:27,928 --> 00:00:31,164
You think I'll get stronger?

14
00:00:31,164 --> 00:00:34,101
♪

15
00:00:34,101 --> 00:00:36,003
Hmm?

16
00:00:36,003 --> 00:00:40,173
♪

17
00:00:40,173 --> 00:00:44,211
It's an odd request,
using my table.

18
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:47,114
♪

19
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:50,517
But I'm not about to
say no to a friend.

20
00:00:50,517 --> 00:00:52,886
Knock yourself out.

21
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,888
Thanks, I owe you one.

22
00:00:56,256 --> 00:00:58,792
Huh?

23
00:00:58,792 --> 00:00:59,660
Hmm.

24
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:03,697
♪

25
00:01:03,697 --> 00:01:05,165
I can picture it.

26
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,237
I've finally obtained
the strength I require

27
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:12,406
to defeat that power.

28
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:17,177
♪

29
00:01:18,946 --> 00:01:24,518
♪

30
00:01:36,463 --> 00:01:45,639
♪

31
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:46,800
♪

32
00:02:50,604 --> 00:02:52,506
(birds chirping)

33
00:03:00,247 --> 00:03:02,482
Blaster Dark.

34
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:06,953
I can always count on you
to get me through my fights.

35
00:03:08,588 --> 00:03:10,857
My dependable avatar.

36
00:03:11,925 --> 00:03:14,027
(gasping)

37
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:17,030
Hello?

38
00:03:18,498 --> 00:03:20,701
Who said that?

39
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:35,749
♪

40
00:03:35,749 --> 00:03:37,184
Hmm, come on, Aichi.

41
00:03:37,184 --> 00:03:39,453
I know you heard it.

42
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:43,090
And what exactly
are you doing here?

43
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:46,793
We didn't invite
you to the shop.

44
00:03:46,793 --> 00:03:48,695
Oh, don't worry about me.

45
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:51,298
I'm just waiting for
a friend to come by.

46
00:03:51,298 --> 00:03:52,599
I don't think so.

47
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:54,000
If you're gonna stand around,

48
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,669
you can do it
out in the mall.

49
00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:58,739
Is this how PSY Shop
treats its customers?

50
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:01,641
Anyway, miss, could you
please grab me a drink?

51
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:05,078
I am not the maid.

52
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,914
You are if you want
to keep my business.

53
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:09,816
(groans)

54
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:14,421
Here's your coffee.

55
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:15,589
(sniffs)

56
00:04:15,589 --> 00:04:18,358
Ah, this garbage is
the best you've got?

57
00:04:18,358 --> 00:04:20,360
(grunts)

58
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,630
♪

59
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,533
Who does he think he is
criticizing my coffee?

60
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:28,034
Now, now.

61
00:04:28,034 --> 00:04:31,037
Hey, how about we close up
the store early today?

62
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,439
He says he's meeting someone,

63
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:34,541
but I don't want to see
any of his friends.

64
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:35,675
Oh?

65
00:04:35,675 --> 00:04:38,712
Well, I wouldn't mind if
that boy came by to visit us.

66
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:39,780
Huh?

67
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,782
You know who
he's waiting for?

68
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:43,950
He's the only
one it could be.

69
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:46,386
Though, it's pretty unlikely
that he'll actually get here.

70
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:48,488
What do you mean?

71
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:51,191
Well, he won't make it

72
00:04:51,191 --> 00:04:53,727
if Kourin has
anything to say about it.

73
00:04:53,727 --> 00:04:55,962
Hold on, she was just‐‐

74
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,264
Now that you mention it,

75
00:04:57,264 --> 00:04:59,633
she's been out
since this morning.

76
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:01,835
♪

77
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:04,037
That voice.

78
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:05,939
I hear it calling me.

79
00:05:05,939 --> 00:05:07,741
Huh?

80
00:05:11,077 --> 00:05:12,813
Kourin, what...

81
00:05:12,813 --> 00:05:15,282
(gasps)

82
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,184
(engine starts)

83
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:23,356
You're coming with me,
Aichi Sendou.

84
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:24,291
(gasps)

85
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:29,296
(footsteps)

86
00:05:29,296 --> 00:05:31,765
You're becoming
too predictable.

87
00:05:31,765 --> 00:05:34,000
(chuckles)

88
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,702
(grunting)

89
00:05:35,702 --> 00:05:37,704
(chuckles)

90
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:40,473
What do you want?

91
00:05:42,209 --> 00:05:44,377
This isn't an easy
question to ask, all right,

92
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:47,080
but you've got to do
something about Aichi.

93
00:05:50,217 --> 00:05:52,152
Kai, we need your help.

94
00:05:52,152 --> 00:05:53,286
You must have noticed

95
00:05:53,286 --> 00:05:55,522
he's been acting really
strange these days.

96
00:05:56,723 --> 00:05:58,091
None of us are blaming you,

97
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,160
but it's gotten a lot
worse since you left.

98
00:06:01,494 --> 00:06:05,198
Aichi, I'm sorry, but I'm
not going to fight you.

99
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:06,433
Huh?

100
00:06:07,267 --> 00:06:08,501
It's been a nightmare.

101
00:06:10,503 --> 00:06:13,006
He's like a different person.

102
00:06:13,006 --> 00:06:15,675
♪

103
00:06:15,675 --> 00:06:16,810
Come on!

104
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:18,345
If you can beat him,
maybe he'll go back

105
00:06:18,345 --> 00:06:19,713
to the way he was!

106
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,681
You think I don't know that?

107
00:06:21,681 --> 00:06:23,516
‐Huh?
‐Hmm.

108
00:06:23,516 --> 00:06:25,418
I'm gonna take care of
this little problem of ours

109
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:26,486
once and for all.

110
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:30,290
The man of the hour is here.

111
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:31,291
Hmm?

112
00:06:31,291 --> 00:06:33,293
(engine putters)

113
00:06:33,293 --> 00:06:36,096
♪

114
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:36,897
(sighs)

115
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:40,634
Hey, Kai.

116
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:42,836
Here, go on.

117
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:44,771
Uh, sure.

118
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:48,308
♪

119
00:06:48,308 --> 00:06:50,477
Got that new deck with you?

120
00:06:50,477 --> 00:06:51,778
Uh...

121
00:06:51,778 --> 00:06:54,714
I challenge you to a fight.

122
00:06:54,714 --> 00:06:55,815
Really?

123
00:06:55,815 --> 00:06:58,151
Last time, you said you
didn't want to battle me.

124
00:06:59,052 --> 00:07:01,521
Yeah, things have changed.

125
00:07:01,521 --> 00:07:03,456
Then does this mean
you've finally recognized

126
00:07:03,456 --> 00:07:04,391
how strong I've gotten?

127
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:06,660
No.

128
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:07,994
You've gotten weaker.

129
00:07:09,462 --> 00:07:10,764
That's rough.

130
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:12,999
Battle me and you'll
see for yourself.

131
00:07:13,967 --> 00:07:15,268
I see.

132
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:18,338
You still think I'm
the player I used to be.

133
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:20,540
Well, if that's
the case then,

134
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:23,843
I'll have to prove to you
how powerful I really am.

135
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:26,513
(worried sighs)

136
00:07:26,513 --> 00:07:29,282
♪

137
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,951
It's in your hands.

138
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:32,085
You can't fail.

139
00:07:34,087 --> 00:07:37,490
Pretty hard to admit that
I'm stronger than you.

140
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,325
Huh, Kai?

141
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:44,531
Why do we have to watch
from way back here?

142
00:07:44,531 --> 00:07:47,434
Uh, this battle is
between the two of them.

143
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:50,270
I think it's best if we
give them a lot of space.

144
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,938
And, trust me,
the battlefield can get

145
00:07:51,938 --> 00:07:53,406
pretty intense at times.

146
00:07:53,406 --> 00:07:54,474
Hmm.

147
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:57,010
Having us out there
would just be distracting.

148
00:07:57,010 --> 00:07:58,979
Okay.

149
00:08:01,414 --> 00:08:04,651
♪

150
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,820
‐Now stand up, the...
‐Now stand up‐‐

151
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,221
‐Vanguard!
‐Vanguard!

152
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:10,123
(whooshing)

153
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,259
Whoa!

154
00:08:13,259 --> 00:08:15,528
I didn't know that was
a motion figure system.

155
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:19,466
I know you can
pull this off, Kai.

156
00:08:19,466 --> 00:08:21,835
Good luck.

157
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:23,069
Go, Fullbau!

158
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:26,039
Barcgal.

159
00:08:26,039 --> 00:08:29,676
♪

160
00:08:29,676 --> 00:08:30,577
You're kidding.

161
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:32,045
That deck.

162
00:08:32,045 --> 00:08:33,380
‐Huh?
‐Yeah.

163
00:08:33,380 --> 00:08:35,982
He's gonna battle him
using the Royal Paladin deck,

164
00:08:35,982 --> 00:08:38,618
the same one Aichi abandoned.

165
00:08:38,618 --> 00:08:40,220
I get it.

166
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:41,921
A cute trick.

167
00:08:41,921 --> 00:08:43,523
You may think
this deck is weak,

168
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,992
but I'm gonna show you how
wrong you are to doubt it.

169
00:08:47,293 --> 00:08:49,429
There's no way you'll
beat the Shadow Paladins.

170
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:51,331
I draw.

171
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:55,335
I ride Blaster Javelin.

172
00:08:55,335 --> 00:08:57,337
♪

173
00:08:57,337 --> 00:09:00,507
Activating Fullbau's skill
to search for my avatar.

174
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,076
Meet Blaster Dark.

175
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:08,248
So you've really given
up on Blaster Blade?

176
00:09:08,248 --> 00:09:14,421
♪

177
00:09:14,421 --> 00:09:15,755
Then I've got no choice

178
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:17,957
but to hit you with
everything I've got.

179
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:22,495
I won't make the
same mistake twice.

180
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:28,768
Four years ago, my parents
went away on a trip,

181
00:09:28,768 --> 00:09:31,071
and never came back.

182
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:33,473
Losing them didn't just hurt,

183
00:09:33,473 --> 00:09:36,609
it shattered my
entire life to pieces.

184
00:09:38,111 --> 00:09:39,646
Everything changed after that.

185
00:09:40,613 --> 00:09:42,882
I was too young
to fend for myself,

186
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:44,884
so my uncle took me in.

187
00:09:44,884 --> 00:09:48,888
I moved away from this town
and left everything behind.

188
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:50,323
It was a fresh start.

189
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:54,327
♪

190
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:56,996
And then I met him.

191
00:09:56,996 --> 00:10:06,573
♪

192
00:10:06,573 --> 00:10:07,707
Huh?

193
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,611
(sighs)

194
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:21,754
♪

195
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:23,823
(footsteps)

196
00:10:25,091 --> 00:10:26,259
This is the guy?

197
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:28,094
That lazy sack of bones
on the ground here

198
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:30,697
is the new Vanguard
fighter from your class?

199
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:31,865
That's right.

200
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:32,899
What's your name?

201
00:10:32,899 --> 00:10:34,434
It's Ren, you know.

202
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:36,302
Not you, dummy, that guy.

203
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:37,437
That guy?

204
00:10:37,437 --> 00:10:39,339
No, they wrote his
name on the board,

205
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:42,208
and it was way
longer than "that guy."

206
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:44,544
Remind me to never
ask you anything again.

207
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,314
New guy, what's
your name, huh?

208
00:10:49,415 --> 00:10:51,551
You don't need
to know my name.

209
00:10:51,551 --> 00:10:53,553
‐What?
‐I'm guessing you woke me up

210
00:10:53,553 --> 00:10:56,556
because you and I
have business, right?

211
00:10:56,556 --> 00:10:59,759
Hmm, you certainly don't
beat around the bush.

212
00:11:05,632 --> 00:11:08,501
‐Stand up, the Vanguard.
‐Stand up, the Vanguard.

213
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:09,903
Wow, cool!

214
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:12,272
The Vanguard.

215
00:11:12,272 --> 00:11:15,942
♪

216
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:23,483
♪

217
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,819
Is that it, Tetsu?

218
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:29,088
‐Well...
‐It's my turn.

219
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:31,524
Now I ride Dragonic Overlord.

220
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:34,093
Burn this world to ashes!

221
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:36,229
Eternal flame!

222
00:11:37,664 --> 00:11:38,665
Hey.

223
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:43,203
Looks like I lost.

224
00:11:44,337 --> 00:11:46,639
Hm, you're not so tough.

225
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:50,710
Getting pushed around
by the new kid?

226
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,478
Be quiet.

227
00:11:52,478 --> 00:11:54,280
So, what do you
think of this guy?

228
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,283
I figure he could
fill the final spot.

229
00:11:57,283 --> 00:11:58,351
Works for me.

230
00:11:58,351 --> 00:11:59,319
Hmm?

231
00:11:59,319 --> 00:12:00,353
You hear that?

232
00:12:00,353 --> 00:12:03,089
You're gonna be a
member of Asteroid.

233
00:12:03,089 --> 00:12:05,024
What's Asteroid?

234
00:12:05,024 --> 00:12:06,893
It's our card fighting team.

235
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:08,728
Though we only started
a little while ago,

236
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:11,397
so it's just me
and Ren right now.

237
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:14,534
Have you heard of the
Vanguard Championships?

238
00:12:14,534 --> 00:12:16,202
It's a team battle.

239
00:12:16,202 --> 00:12:17,971
In order to compete
at the national level,

240
00:12:17,971 --> 00:12:20,406
you have to have a group
of at least three players.

241
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:23,409
Now that you're here, we've
finally got enough to compete.

242
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:26,412
So you guys want
me on your team?

243
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:30,216
Yeah, I'm Tetsu Shinjou,
and this here is...

244
00:12:30,216 --> 00:12:31,618
Your name's Ren, right?

245
00:12:31,618 --> 00:12:34,520
Yeah, Ren Suzugamori
at your service.

246
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,455
Come on.

247
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:37,190
You wanna join the team?

248
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:40,026
Are you sure that I'm...

249
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:42,295
Look, you were strong
enough to defeat me,

250
00:12:42,295 --> 00:12:43,296
and more importantly,

251
00:12:43,296 --> 00:12:45,798
Ren seems to have
taking a liking to you.

252
00:12:45,798 --> 00:12:47,500
Why does that matter?

253
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,068
Ren's a bit weird,

254
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:50,737
but he's also a good
judge of character,

255
00:12:50,737 --> 00:12:52,272
so you must be a cool guy.

256
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:54,207
Hmm.

257
00:12:56,175 --> 00:12:58,645
Do you mind if I take
a look at your deck?

258
00:12:58,645 --> 00:12:59,679
Uh, sure.

259
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,549
So you want to go to the
Vanguard Championship?

260
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:05,151
Then count me in.

261
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:07,520
‐Nice.
‐My name's Kai.

262
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,821
Toshiki Kai.

263
00:13:08,821 --> 00:13:10,657
Put her there, teammate.

264
00:13:10,657 --> 00:13:12,292
Ha, sure.

265
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:14,127
Hey, what are you guys doing?

266
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:16,763
Shouldn't that be
a team handshake?

267
00:13:16,763 --> 00:13:22,769
♪

268
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:25,338
We set our sights
on the championship,

269
00:13:25,338 --> 00:13:26,873
but back then, Team Asteroid

270
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:28,675
was still in the
learning stages.

271
00:13:31,177 --> 00:13:33,146
Tetsu's play was
really undisciplined,

272
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,114
and he made
a lot of mistakes.

273
00:13:35,114 --> 00:13:36,416
Ren would keep our spirits up

274
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,351
with the ridiculous
things he said.

275
00:13:38,351 --> 00:13:41,154
He was always
good for a laugh.

276
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,156
♪

277
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:45,491
They were the best
friends I'd ever had.

278
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:48,294
Being with them
made me feel at home.

279
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:49,996
Those were good times.

280
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:53,032
Sadly, it didn't last.

281
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:56,936
Wasn't I clear?

282
00:13:56,936 --> 00:13:59,339
Guarding isn't going
to help you at all.

283
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:01,074
I told you at
the very beginning

284
00:14:01,074 --> 00:14:02,475
that I would beat
you with this card

285
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:04,911
no matter what you do.

286
00:14:04,911 --> 00:14:06,279
Huh?

287
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:08,147
(sighs)

288
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:10,049
(shouts)

289
00:14:11,651 --> 00:14:13,786
Hey!

290
00:14:13,786 --> 00:14:15,555
Are you okay?

291
00:14:15,555 --> 00:14:17,490
Yeah, don't worry.

292
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:18,825
Huh?

293
00:14:18,825 --> 00:14:21,027
Shows you for resisting.

294
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:25,431
♪

295
00:14:25,431 --> 00:14:26,899
It's a shame, Tetsu.

296
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:28,868
I thought you were
a better player.

297
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,503
You disappoint me.

298
00:14:30,503 --> 00:14:31,504
Stop it!

299
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:32,805
Yeah, you were
able to beat him,

300
00:14:32,805 --> 00:14:34,540
but you don't
need to be a jerk.

301
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:35,875
I was able to?

302
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,643
I don't think you understand.

303
00:14:37,643 --> 00:14:38,811
What?

304
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:41,247
Well, why don't you let him
know what's happening to me?

305
00:14:42,782 --> 00:14:47,587
Ren is stronger, and it's
almost scary at this point.

306
00:14:47,587 --> 00:14:49,555
Scary, how come?

307
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:52,759
You see, I've been
reborn as a card fighter.

308
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:54,727
I don't like this.

309
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,262
I can hear them speak.

310
00:14:56,262 --> 00:14:58,498
The cards are talking.

311
00:14:58,498 --> 00:14:59,565
Talking?

312
00:14:59,565 --> 00:15:00,900
But how?

313
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,436
It's all thanks to this
incredible new power

314
00:15:03,436 --> 00:15:04,904
I've obtained, Kai.

315
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:08,040
Now no one will be able
to stand in my way.

316
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:11,144
You're looking at the
strongest card fighter on earth.

317
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:13,146
(laughing)

318
00:15:13,146 --> 00:15:19,685
♪

319
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:22,588
What was this power
Ren had discovered?

320
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:25,525
At the time, I had no idea.

321
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:27,627
But what was clear was
that Ren was no longer

322
00:15:27,627 --> 00:15:29,195
the same guy I once knew.

323
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:34,767
(drilling)

324
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:38,171
What is this place?

325
00:15:38,171 --> 00:15:40,273
Asteroid's new headquarters.

326
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:41,274
Hmm?

327
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:43,176
I'm gonna gather and
train fighters here

328
00:15:43,176 --> 00:15:45,778
until we're the best
team in the whole world.

329
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:46,446
But why?

330
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:48,247
We've already got a team.

331
00:15:48,247 --> 00:15:51,150
Ren's got some new plans
for the future of our group.

332
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:52,418
Hmm?

333
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:53,786
The top players
in the country

334
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:55,555
will be brought here
to battle each other

335
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:59,392
with the winners moving on
to bigger, better fights.

336
00:15:59,392 --> 00:16:03,029
Only those few that can prove
themselves by going undefeated

337
00:16:03,029 --> 00:16:06,232
will earn the honor of
playing for Team Asteroid.

338
00:16:06,232 --> 00:16:08,034
This all seems like
a waste of time,

339
00:16:08,034 --> 00:16:10,770
considering that we
have a full roster.

340
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:12,505
There's no free rides here.

341
00:16:12,505 --> 00:16:16,108
You've got to fight for a
spot just like everyone else.

342
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:18,244
But I'm sure you
can handle it.

343
00:16:20,746 --> 00:16:22,648
Oh, yeah?

344
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,650
You're very talented, Kai.

345
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:27,487
You and I, together with
our army of elite fighters,

346
00:16:27,487 --> 00:16:29,755
can conquer the
world of Vanguard!

347
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:32,124
No chance.

348
00:16:32,124 --> 00:16:33,025
Huh?

349
00:16:35,394 --> 00:16:38,030
‐Get your deck.
‐But...

350
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:40,733
I'll show you who's
the strongest right now.

351
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:42,869
(grunts)

352
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:48,040
All right, stand
up the Vanguard.

353
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:54,914
♪

354
00:16:54,914 --> 00:16:56,749
I wanted to beat Ren

355
00:16:56,749 --> 00:16:59,685
to show him that Vanguard
wasn't about being the best.

356
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,487
It was about
enjoying the game

357
00:17:01,487 --> 00:17:04,757
and the friendship
we'd created, only...

358
00:17:04,757 --> 00:17:06,092
Final turn.

359
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,262
Can you see it?

360
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:11,631
You're broken and
utterly defeated

361
00:17:11,631 --> 00:17:14,133
on the surface of
the Planet Cray.

362
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,368
It's pathetic.

363
00:17:15,368 --> 00:17:17,670
(gasps)

364
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:18,804
Huh?

365
00:17:18,804 --> 00:17:21,474
♪

366
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:23,743
Th‐‐this is...

367
00:17:23,743 --> 00:17:26,946
So, Kai, like my winning image?

368
00:17:26,946 --> 00:17:28,848
Ren, get me out of here!

369
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:30,616
No.

370
00:17:30,616 --> 00:17:33,553
I want you to fully
understand my new powers,

371
00:17:33,553 --> 00:17:36,589
and I want you to appreciate
how helpless you really are.

372
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,225
This is the end of the line.

373
00:17:40,326 --> 00:17:43,496
Now, say hello to my
avatar, Blaster Dark!

374
00:17:44,497 --> 00:17:45,798
Oh!

375
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:49,268
♪

376
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:52,738
You're not the same
person I used to know.

377
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:55,508
Rising from the shadows
to cut down my enemies.

378
00:17:55,508 --> 00:17:59,111
Go, I'll destroy anyone
that interferes with me!

379
00:17:59,111 --> 00:18:01,180
(laughs)

380
00:18:03,049 --> 00:18:04,951
(grunts)

381
00:18:06,886 --> 00:18:09,288
(groans)

382
00:18:09,288 --> 00:18:10,289
Ren!

383
00:18:12,258 --> 00:18:13,225
(grunts)

384
00:18:15,361 --> 00:18:16,195
Careful!

385
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:17,296
What's wrong with you?

386
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:22,602
Kai, I‐‐I've gotten
much stronger.

387
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:24,203
Oh.

388
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:33,279
♪

389
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:34,780
Leaving?

390
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:37,583
You can come with
me if you want.

391
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:39,485
I'll never turn
my back on him.

392
00:18:41,053 --> 00:18:42,321
Yeah.

393
00:18:44,357 --> 00:18:45,891
I left.

394
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:47,426
Unable to stop Ren,

395
00:18:47,426 --> 00:18:50,796
I decided to get as far
away from him as I could.

396
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:56,402
♪

397
00:18:56,402 --> 00:18:59,839
So I moved back home
for another fresh start.

398
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:02,975
Kai!

399
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,510
Kai, is that you?

400
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:07,146
Oh, man, it really is!

401
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:09,615
Remember, it's me, Miwa.

402
00:19:09,615 --> 00:19:10,616
How you been?

403
00:19:10,616 --> 00:19:12,218
Leave me alone.

404
00:19:12,218 --> 00:19:13,819
Hold on, hey!

405
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,388
We used to be pals!

406
00:19:16,956 --> 00:19:19,558
I couldn't forgive myself.

407
00:19:19,558 --> 00:19:21,227
I'd lost my best friends

408
00:19:21,227 --> 00:19:24,196
because I wasn't strong
enough to stop Ren,

409
00:19:24,196 --> 00:19:26,666
and it ate me up inside.

410
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:29,068
I thought about
it constantly,

411
00:19:29,068 --> 00:19:30,603
how different things
might have been

412
00:19:30,603 --> 00:19:32,872
if I wasn't so weak.

413
00:19:32,872 --> 00:19:34,707
If only I'd been
able to overwhelm

414
00:19:34,707 --> 00:19:36,342
that Psyqualia of his.

415
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:41,380
All I cared about was becoming
a stronger card fighter,

416
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:44,350
always searching
for the next challenge.

417
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,584
Then, one day...

418
00:19:47,053 --> 00:19:49,922
Um, that card
means a lot to me.

419
00:19:49,922 --> 00:19:52,558
Look, I just won this
in a game of Vanguard,

420
00:19:52,558 --> 00:19:54,994
so there's no way that
I'm gonna give it up easily.

421
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:58,297
Mm, fine then!

422
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:00,933
I'll fight you
to get it back!

423
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,768
Okay, kid, it's a deal.

424
00:20:04,837 --> 00:20:07,640
‐Now stand up, the Vanguard.
‐Now stand up, the Vanguard.

425
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:10,376
♪

426
00:20:11,911 --> 00:20:14,146
He didn't stand a
chance against me,

427
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:17,483
but I took it slow and
I taught him the rules.

428
00:20:17,483 --> 00:20:19,351
Normally, I wouldn't
even waste my time

429
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:21,253
playing someone so weak.

430
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:23,089
But...

431
00:20:23,089 --> 00:20:25,791
Now stand up, my avatar!

432
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:27,927
I ride Blaster Blade.

433
00:20:27,927 --> 00:20:31,664
♪

434
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:32,398
Hmm.

435
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:37,169
I realized I was actually
enjoying Vanguard again.

436
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:41,674
The game had become such
a struggle for power.

437
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:43,776
(laughing)

438
00:20:43,776 --> 00:20:47,079
♪

439
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,115
I'd forgotten.

440
00:20:49,115 --> 00:20:51,484
Card fights were
supposed to be fun.

441
00:20:51,484 --> 00:20:55,421
♪

442
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:58,691
You made it possible for me
to see that again, Aichi.

443
00:21:00,693 --> 00:21:02,862
Only now...

444
00:21:02,862 --> 00:21:06,065
♪

445
00:21:06,065 --> 00:21:08,467
I'm stronger now, right?

446
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,069
Then why don't you fight me,

447
00:21:10,069 --> 00:21:12,838
and I'll prove to you exactly
how strong I've become!

448
00:21:12,838 --> 00:21:15,141
You know that if
we play, I'll win.

449
00:21:15,141 --> 00:21:18,010
♪

450
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:20,646
I lost a friend
once to Psyqualia,

451
00:21:20,646 --> 00:21:23,249
but this time
will be different.

452
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:24,650
I'm gonna stop you.

453
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:26,752
I won't let it happen again.

454
00:21:26,752 --> 00:21:29,455
♪

455
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:32,358
I'll start by riding
Young Pegasus Knight,

456
00:21:32,358 --> 00:21:35,761
then I move Barcgal and use
his ability to call Flogal.

457
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:39,732
♪

458
00:21:39,732 --> 00:21:42,835
Gancelot's skill,
I search for Blaster Blade

459
00:21:42,835 --> 00:21:44,403
and add it to my hand.

460
00:21:45,704 --> 00:21:48,140
Blaster Blade, huh?

461
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,675
Don't you remember?

462
00:21:49,675 --> 00:21:51,777
It's your avatar.

463
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:55,047
Oh, I know, but I don't
care about that card anymore

464
00:21:55,047 --> 00:21:57,349
because now I've got a
much stronger avatar.

465
00:21:58,884 --> 00:22:00,186
Wrong.

466
00:22:00,186 --> 00:22:01,687
Hm?

467
00:22:01,687 --> 00:22:03,823
It doesn't matter if
you threw it away or not,

468
00:22:03,823 --> 00:22:06,859
your avatar is always
going to be Blaster Blade.

469
00:22:06,859 --> 00:22:08,360
Hm!

470
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:10,729
Aichi, the time has come
for me to teach you

471
00:22:10,729 --> 00:22:13,566
what true strength really is.

472
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:16,869
All right!

473
00:22:16,869 --> 00:22:19,271
Your quest for
power ends now!

474
00:22:19,271 --> 00:22:22,541
♪

475
00:22:26,812 --> 00:22:35,087
♪

476
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:03,509
I'll force you to acknowledge
my strength if I have to.

477
00:24:03,509 --> 00:24:05,377
Aichi, it's my fault

478
00:24:05,377 --> 00:24:07,813
you care so much
about getting stronger.

479
00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:08,914
Don't say that.

480
00:24:08,914 --> 00:24:11,216
You taught me everything
I know about card fighting.

481
00:24:11,216 --> 00:24:14,787
And you helped me remember
how fun this game really is.

482
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:17,790
I've come so far to stand
across from you as an equal.

483
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:19,992
I'm ready to destroy you.

484
00:24:19,992 --> 00:24:22,761
Next time, "At the
End of the Battle..."

485
00:24:22,761 --> 00:24:26,298
I see Kai broken on the
surface of the Planet Cray.

486
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:28,200
♪

